[The item above also includes fragments derived from an International
Herald Tribune/Associated Press newswire dated 5 Nov 2008 (see at
<http://www.iht.com/articles/ap/2008/11/05/europe/EU-Austria-Livestock-Disease.php>).
A confirmation from the EU reference laboratory, addressing the serotype
(which is, most likely, BTV-8) is anticipated.

An official notification of this outbreak to the OIE (World Organisation
for Animal Health), with the available additional information on the
epidemiological and laboratory investigations, is expected soon.

The Upper Austrian areas, which have now been demarcated by Austria as
"surveillance and/or protection zones... in accordance with Article 8 of
Council Directive 2000/75/EC" are included in Zone F (namely the zone where
BTV-8 may be circulating or where vaccination against it is applied) and
can be seen on the table, updated as of 5 Nov 2008, at
<http://ec.europa.eu/food/animal/diseases/controlmeasures/bt_restrictedzones.pdf>.

The active disease season is expected to terminate towards the end of
November (2008), with the decrease of temperatures and of the vector
activity. - Mod.AS

Schaerding in Upper Austria (Oberoesterreich) can be located on the map at
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/europe/austria_pol99.jpg>. The
HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Austria is available at
<http://healthmap.org/promed?g=2766155&v=47.45,13.433,6>. - CopyEd.MJ]
